<div class="format_text" id="comment-body-43939">
<p>I was ready to purchase from Gainesville Coins. I was led to this website from Google after reading about a promo code for free shipping.  I had read on several websites that GC&#8217;s were very reputable, won the best bouillon award given by the NIA, BBB A+ (not sure the BBB means much from my experience) and a few websites with reviews had positive things to say about their customer service, delivery, prices, etc.  How in the heck does a meager consumer looking to buy some gold bars, $50, 24 Karat buffalo nickels know where to go so they will not get ripped off?  I know with the market&#8217;s situation it is very hard to find a place to get real,pure gold bars that are not &#8220;plastic in the center and gold on the outside?&#8221;  I would like to make some rather small gold investments but I can&#8217;t afford to get ripped off.  I am using the money for my chemotherapy to buy some real, pure, gold that has some sound accreditations (APMEX I assume would be one) behind the company.  Can Trace Mayer, JD shoot me any recommendations?  Is it even possible for novices to get real gold at a decent price (not so far from the NY Stock Exchange closing prices for gold-maybe referred to as SPOT pricing)?  any advice would be greatly appreciated. I have read so many websites and research papers on various companies and the ore I read the more confide I get.  I just want to know is it possible if this is not your occupation to get some gold bars and not get ripped off?  Please help.  I had heard that Gainesville Coins was a repeatable place and now on here I read the complete opposite.  I just want to invest a little because I have a little and I am so sick of being sick from my chemo, I figured I am getting reedy to give up on chemo and spend the money on something like some gold, but the real stuff and not get ripped off by paying such high prices and tons of extra fees that it turns out the investment could never reconsidered an investment at all.  Any names of real places to go and not more articles to read that just makes me more confused??</p>
</div>
